: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n46: \n47: docker-buildx-push:\n48: \tdocker buildx build \\\n49: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n50: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n51: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=linux \\\n52: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 \\\n53: \t\t--push \\\n54: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n55: \t\t.\n56: \n57: docker-buildx-push-router:\n58: \tdocker buildx build \\\n59: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n60: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n61: \t\t--push \\\n62: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n63: \t\t.\n64: \n65: docker-buildx-push-picod:\n66: \tdocker buildx build \\\n67: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n68: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n69: \t\t--push \\\n70: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n71: \t\t.\n\n(End of file - total 71 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":".PHONY: all build test clean docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod docker-build-all docker-buildx-push docker-buildx-push-router docker-buildx-push-picod\n\nIMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\nVERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"latest\")\nTARGETOS ?= linux\nTARGETARCH ?= amd64\n\nall: build\n\nbuild:\n\tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n\tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n\tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n\ntest:\n\tgo test -v ./...\n\nclean:\n\trm -rf bin/\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/Makefile","time":{"start":1775887713961,"end":1775887713976}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887713999,"sessionID":"ses_284d84384ffevCk417TTr8aPCs","part":{"id":"prt_d7b27feda001O5FV0ZNv0MYaHd","messageID":"msg_d7b27e583001VYyXdBY1R6MBi4","sessionID":"ses_284d84384ffevCk417TTr8aPCs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-ca9121c34e494fcb807aa3bab7007e83","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系 |\n8: | Module | `root` |\n9: | Language | Makefile |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 (completed) |\n12: \n13: Comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, providing unified build interface across all binaries (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox), quality gates (lint, test, coverage), Docker image targets, E2E test orchestration, and developer-friendly `make help` documentation.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### High-Level Architecture\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                          Makefile Build Target System                              │\n24: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n25: │                                                                                   │\n26: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n27: │   │                        Variable Layer                                     │   │\n28: │   │   IMAGE_REPO, VERSION, TARGETOS, TARGETARCH, BINDIR, INSTALL_PREFIX      │   │\n29: │   │   GO_VERSION, GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION, CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION            │   │\n30: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n31: │                                    │                                              │\n32: │                                    ▼                                              │\n33: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n34: │   │                        Target Categories                                  │   │\n35: │   │                                                                           │   │\n36: │   │   ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐               │   │\n37: │   │   │ Build Targets │  │ Test Targets  │  │ Quality Targets│               │   │\n38: │   │   │───────────────│  │───────────────│  │───────────────│               │   │\n39: │   │   │ all           │  │ test          │  │ lint          │               │   │\n40: │   │   │ build         │  │ test-coverage │  │ fmt           │               │   │\n41: │   │   │ build-*       │  │ test-race     │  │ vet           │               │   │\n42: │   │   │ build-linux-* │  │               │  │ gen-check     │               │   │\n43: │   │   │ build-darwin-*│  │               │  │ gen-copyright │               │   │\n44: │   │   └───────────────┘  └───────────────┘  └───────────────┘               │   │\n45: │   │                                                                           │   │\n46: │   │   ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐               │   │\n47: │   │   │ Docker Targets│  │ E2E Targets   │  │ Install Targets│               │   │\n48: │   │   │───────────────│  │───────────────│  │───────────────│               │   │\n49: │   │   │ docker-build  │  │ e2e           │  │ install       │               │   │\n50: │   │   │ docker-build-*│  │ e2e-setup     │  │ install-*     │               │   │\n51: │   │   │ docker-buildx │  │ e2e-clean     │  │               │               │   │\n52: │   │   │ docker-push-* │  │               │  │               │               │   │\n53: │   │   └───────────────┘  └───────────────┘  └───────────────┘               │   │\n54: │   │                                                                           │   │\n55: │   │   ┌───────────────┐  ┌───────────────┐                                   │   │\n56: │   │   │ Clean Targets │  │ Help Target   │                                   │   │\n57: │   │   │───────────────│  │───────────────│                                   │   │\n58: │   │   │ clean         │  │ help          │                                   │   │\n59: │   │   │ clean-test    │  │               │                                   │   │\n60: │   │   └───────────────┘  └───────────────┘                                   │   │\n61: │   │                                                                           │   │\n62: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n63: │                                    │                                              │\n64: │                                    ▼                                              │\n65: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n66: │   │                        Tool Dependencies                                  │   │\n67: │   │   go (1.24+), golangci-lint, docker, docker buildx, kind, helm, git     │   │\n68: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n69: │                                    │                                              │\n70: │                                    ▼                                              │\n71: │   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n72: │   │                        Output Artifacts                                   │   │\n73: │   │   bin/*, coverage.out, coverage.html, docker images, Kind cluster       │   │\n74: │   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n75: │                                                                                   │\n76: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Build Target Flow\n80: \n81: ```\n82: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n83: │                        Build Target Flow                                      │\n84: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n85: │                                                                              │\n86: │   make (default: all)                                                        │\n87: │        │                                                                     │\n88: │        ▼                                                                     │\n89: │   all → build                                                                │\n90: │        │                                                                     │\n91: │        ├─► generate (controller-gen object, gen-crd)                        │\n92: │        │                                                                     │\n93: │        ├─► build-workloadmanager                                            │\n94: │        │        go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager      │\n95: │        │                                                                     │\n96: │        ├─► build-router                                                      │\n97: │        │        go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router                         │\n98: │        │                                                                     │\n99: │        ├─► build-picod                                                       │\n100: │        │        go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod                           │\n101: │        │                                                                     │\n102: │        ├─► build-agentd                                                      │\n103: │        │        go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd                         │\n104: │        │                                                                     │\n105: │        ├─► build-agentctl                                                    │\n106: │        │        go build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl                     │\n107: │        │                                                                     │\n108: │        ├─► build-agentcube                                                   │\n109: │        │        go build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube                    │\n110: │        │                                                                     │\n111: │        └─► build-agentsandbox                                               │\n112: │                 go build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox             │\n113: │                                                                              │\n114: │   Cross-compile targets (GOOS/GOARCH):                                       │\n115: │   build-linux-amd64  → GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build ...                 │\n116: │   build-linux-arm64  → GOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build ...                 │\n117: │   build-darwin-amd64 → GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build ...                │\n118: │   build-darwin-arm64 → GOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build ...                │\n119: │                                                                              │\n120: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### Test Target Flow\n124: \n125: ```\n126: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n127: │                        Test Target Flow                                       │\n128: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n129: │                                                                              │\n130: │   make test                                                                  │\n131: │        │                                                                     │\n132: │        ▼                                                                     │\n133: │   go test -v ./...                                                           │\n134: │        │                                                                     │\n135: │        ├─► pkg/... (package tests)                                          │\n136: │        ├─► cmd/... (command tests)                                          │\n137: │        └─► client-go/... (client tests)                                     │\n138: │                                                                              │\n139: │   make test-coverage                                                         │\n140: │        │                                                                     │\n141: │        ├─► go test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...                         │\n142: │        ├─► go tool cover -func=coverage.out (terminal output)               │\n143: │        └─► go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html                │\n144: │                                                                              │\n145: │   make test-race                                                             │\n146: │        │                                                                     │\n147: │        ▼                                                                     │\n148: │   go test -race ./...                                                        │\n149: │                                                                              │\n150: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Docker Build Target Flow\n154: \n155: ```\n156: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n157: │                        Docker Build Target Flow                               │\n158: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n159: │                                                                              │\n160: │   make docker-build                                                          │\n161: │        │                                                                     │\n162: │        ▼                                                                     │\n163: │   docker build -f docker/Dockerfile                                          │\n164: │        -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)                           │\n165: │        --build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS)                                      │\n166: │        --build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH)                                  │\n167: │        .                                                                     │\n168: │                                                                              │\n169: │   make docker-build-router                                                   │\n170: │        │                                                                     │\n171: │        ▼                                                                     │\n172: │   docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router                                   │\n173: │        -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION)                                    │\n174: │        .                                                                     │\n175: │                                                                              │\n176: │   make docker-build-picod                                                    │\n177: │        │                                                                     │\n178: │        ▼                                                                     │\n179: │   docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod                                    │\n180: │        -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION)                                     │\n181: │        .                                                                     │\n182: │                                                                              │\n183: │   make docker-build-all                                                      │\n184: │        │                                                                     │\n185: │        ├─► docker-build                                                      │\n186: │        ├─► docker-build-router                                               │\n187: │        └─► docker-build-picod                                                │\n188: │                                                                              │\n189: │   make docker-buildx-push-*                                                  │\n190: │        │                                                                     │\n191: │        ▼                                                                     │\n192: │   docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64                     │\n193: │        --push -t $(IMAGE_REPO)/<image>:$(VERSION)                            │\n194: │                                                                              │\n195: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n196: ```\n197: \n198: ### E2E Test Target Flow\n199: \n200: ```\n201: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n202: │                        E2E Target Flow                                        │\n203: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n204: │                                                                              │\n205: │   make e2e                                                                   │\n206: │        │                                                                     │\n207: │        ▼                                                                     │\n208: │   ./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh                                                      │\n209: │        │                                                                     │\n210: │        ├─► kind create cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)                   │\n211: │        ├─► kubectl apply CRDs + agent-sandbox                               │\n212: │        ├─► make docker-build-all                                            │\n213: │        ├─► kind load docker-image ...                                       │\n214: │        ├─► helm upgrade --install agentcube ...                             │\n215: │        ├─► kubectl port-forward svc/workloadmanager                         │\n216: │        ├─► kubectl port-forward svc/agentcube-router                        │\n217: │        ├─► go test -v ./test/e2e/...                                        │\n218: │        ├─► python test_codeinterpreter.py                                   │\n219: │        └─► collect_component_logs (on failure)                              │\n220: │                                                                              │\n221: │   make e2e-clean                                                             │\n222: │        │                                                                     │\n223: │        ├─► kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)                   │\n224: │        └─► rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox                                        │\n225: │                                                                              │\n226: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n227: ```\n228: \n229: ### CI Workflow Integration\n230: \n231: ```\n232: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n233: │                          CI/CD Pipeline Integration                            │\n234: ├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n235: │                                                                               │\n236: │   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n237: │   │                     GitHub Actions Workflows                           │  │\n238: │   │                                                                        │  │\n239: │   │   .github/workflows/main.yml                                           │  │\n240: │   │       ├─► make docker-build                                            │  │\n241: │   │                                                                        │  │\n242: │   │   .github/workflows/lint.yml                                           │  │\n243: │   │       ├─► make lint                                                    │  │\n244: │   │                                                                        │  │\n245: │   │   .github/workflows/test-coverage.yml                                  │  │\n246: │   │       ├─► go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out ...              │  │\n247: │   │       ├─► (coverage targets wrap this for local use)                   │  │\n248: │   │                                                                        │  │\n249: │   │   .github/workflows/e2e.yml                                            │  │\n250: │   │       ├─► make e2e                                                     │  │\n251: │   │       ├─► (always) make e2e-clean                                      │  │\n252: │   │                                                                        │  │\n253: │   │   .github/workflows/codegen-check.yml                                  │  │\n254: │   │       ├─► make gen-check                                               │  │\n255: │   │                                                                        │  │\n256: │   │   .github/workflows/copyright-check.yml                                │  │\n257: │   │       ├─► make gen-copyright                                           │  │\n258: │   │                                                                        │  │\n259: │   │   .github/workflows/build-push-release.yml                             │  │\n260: │   │       ├─► make docker-buildx-push                                      │  │\n261: │   │       ├─► make docker-buildx-push-router                               │  │\n262: │   │       ├─► make docker-buildx-push-picod                                │  │\n263: │   │                                                                        │  │\n264: │   └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n265: │                                                                               │\n266: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n267: ```\n268: \n269: ### Component Relationships\n270: \n271: | Component | Purpose |\n272: |-----------|---------|\n273: | `Makefile` | Central build orchestration file |\n274: | `go.mod/go.sum` | Go module dependency definitions |\n275: | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Multi-stage Docker build definitions |\n276: | `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` | E2E test orchestration script |\n277: | `hack/*.sh` | Codegen and copyright scripts |\n278: | `pkg/apis/` | CRD API definitions (codegen input) |\n279: | `manifests/charts/base/` | Helm chart for deployment |\n280: | `.github/workflows/` | CI workflow definitions |\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Data Structures\n285: \n286: ### Binary Target Definition\n287: \n288: ```yaml\n289: BinaryTarget:\n290:   name: string              # Target name (e.g., build-picod)\n291:   source_path: string       # Go source directory (e.g., ./cmd/picod)\n292:   output_name: string       # Binary name (e.g., picod)\n293:   output_path: string       # Full output path (e.g., bin/picod)\n294:   ldflags: string           # Linker flags (default: \"-w -s\")\n295:   cgo_enabled: boolean      # CGO setting (default: false)\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ### Binary Inventory\n299: \n300: ```yaml\n301: Binaries:\n302:   - name: workloadmanager\n303:     source_path: ./cmd/workload-manager\n304:     output_path: bin/workloadmanager\n305:     dockerfile: docker/Dockerfile\n306:     image_name: workloadmanager\n307:     \n308:   - name: router\n309:     source_path: ./cmd/router\n310:     output_path: bin/router\n311:     dockerfile: docker/Dockerfile.router\n312:     image_name: router\n313:     \n314:   - name: picod\n315:     source_path: ./cmd/picod\n316:     output_path: bin/picod\n317:     dockerfile: docker/Dockerfile.picod\n318:     image_name: picod\n319:     \n320:   - name: agentd\n321:     source_path: ./cmd/agentd\n322:     output_path: bin/agentd\n323:     dockerfile: null          # No dedicated Dockerfile\n324:     \n325:   - name: agentctl\n326:     source_path: ./cmd/agentctl\n327:     output_path: bin/agentctl\n328:     dockerfile: null\n329:     \n330:   - name: agentcube\n331:     source_path: ./cmd/agentcube\n332:     output_path: bin/agentcube\n333:     dockerfile: null\n334:     \n335:   - name: agentsandbox\n336:     source_path: ./cmd/agentsandbox\n337:     output_path: bin/agentsandbox\n338:     dockerfile: null\n339: ```\n340: \n341: ### Variable System\n342: \n343: ```yaml\n344: Variables:\n345:   IMAGE_REPO:\n346:     type: string\n347:     default: \"ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\"\n348:     override: \"?=\" syntax\n349:     description: \"Docker image repository base URL\"\n350:     \n351:   VERSION:\n352:     type: string\n353:     default: \"$(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo latest)\"\n354:     override: \"?=\" syntax\n355:     description: \"Image version tag\"\n356:     \n357:   TARGETOS:\n358:     type: string\n359:     default: \"linux\"\n360:     values: [\"linux\", \"darwin\", \"windows\"]\n361:     description: \"Target operating system for cross-compilation\"\n362:     \n363:   TARGETARCH:\n364:     type: string\n365:     default: \"amd64\"\n366:     values: [\"amd64\", \"arm64\", \"arm\", \"386\"]\n367:     description: \"Target architecture for cross-compilation\"\n368:     \n369:   GO_VERSION:\n370:     type: string\n371:     default: \"1.24\"\n372:     description: \"Go toolchain version for CI alignment\"\n373:     \n374:   GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION:\n375:     type: string\n376:     default: \"1.64.7\"\n377:     description: \"golangci-lint version for CI alignment\"\n378:     \n379:   CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION:\n380:     type: string\n381:     default: \"v0.17.2\"\n382:     description: \"controller-gen version for codegen\"\n383:     \n384:   BINDIR:\n385:     type: string\n386:     default: \"bin/\"\n387:     description: \"Output directory for compiled binaries\"\n388:     \n389:   INSTALL_PREFIX:\n390:     type: string\n391:     default: \"$(shell go env GOPATH)/bin\"\n392:     description: \"Installation destination for binaries\"\n393:     \n394:   LOCALBIN:\n395:     type: string\n396:     default: \"$(shell pwd)/bin\"\n397:     description: \"Local tool installation directory\"\n398:     \n399:   CONTROLLER_GEN:\n400:     type: string\n401:     default: \"$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen\"\n402:     description: \"controller-gen binary path\"\n403:     \n404:   GOLANGCI_LINT:\n405:     type: string\n406:     default: \"$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint\"\n407:     description: \"golangci-lint binary path\"\n408:     \n409:   E2E_CLUSTER_NAME:\n410:     type: string\n411:     default: \"agentcube-e2e\"\n412:     description: \"Kind cluster name for E2E tests\"\n413:     \n414:   HUB:\n415:     type: string\n416:     default: \"ghcr.io/volcano-sh\"\n417:     description: \"Image registry hub\"\n418:     \n419:   WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE:\n420:     type: string\n421:     default: \"workloadmanager:latest\"\n422:     description: \"Workload manager image name\"\n423:     \n424:   ROUTER_IMAGE:\n425:     type: string\n426:     default: \"agentcube-router:latest\"\n427:     description: \"Router image name\"\n428:     \n429:   PICOD_IMAGE:\n430:     type: string\n431:     default: \"picod:latest\"\n432:     description: \"Picod image name\"\n433:     \n434:   IMAGE_REGISTRY:\n435:     type: string\n436:     default: \"\"\n437:     description: \"Registry override for push targets\"\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ### Target Category Structure\n441: \n442: ```yaml\n443: TargetCategories:\n444:   build:\n445:     targets:\n446:       - all\n447:       - build\n448:       - build-workloadmanager\n449:       - build-router\n450:       - build-picod\n451:       - build-agentd\n452:       - build-agentctl\n453:       - build-agentcube\n454:       - build-agentsandbox\n455:       - build-all\n456:       - build-linux-amd64\n457:       - build-linux-arm64\n458:       - build-darwin-amd64\n459:       - build-darwin-arm64\n460:     phony: true\n461:     \n462:   test:\n463:     targets:\n464:       - test\n465:       - test-coverage\n466:       - test-race\n467:     phony: true\n468:     \n469:   quality:\n470:     targets:\n471:       - lint\n472:       - fmt\n473:       - vet\n474:       - gen-check\n475:       - gen-copyright\n476:     phony: true\n477:     \n478:   docker:\n479:     targets:\n480:       - docker-build\n481:       - docker-build-router\n482:       - docker-build-picod\n483:       - docker-build-all\n484:       - docker-buildx\n485:       - docker-buildx-router\n486:       - docker-buildx-picod\n487:       - docker-buildx-push\n488:       - docker-buildx-push-router\n489:       - docker-buildx-push-picod\n490:       - docker-push\n491:       - docker-push-router\n492:       - docker-push-picod\n493:       - kind-load\n494:       - kind-load-router\n495:       - kind-load-picod\n496:     phony: true\n497:     \n498:   e2e:\n499:     targets:\n500:       - e2e\n501:       - e2e-setup\n502:       - e2e-clean\n503:     phony: true\n504:     \n505:   install:\n506:     targets:\n507:       - install\n508:       - install-workloadmanager\n509:       - install-router\n510:       - install-picod\n511:       - install-agentd\n512:       - install-agentctl\n513:       - install-agentcube\n514:       - install-agentsandbox\n515:     phony: true\n516:     \n517:   clean:\n518:     targets:\n519:       - clean\n520:       - clean-test\n521:       - clean-bin\n522:     phony: true\n523:     \n524:   codegen:\n525:     targets:\n526:       - generate\n527:       - gen-crd\n528:       - gen-client\n529:       - gen-all\n530:     phony: true\n531:     \n532:   help:\n533:     targets:\n534:       - help\n535:     phony: true\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ---\n539: \n540: ## API Contracts\n541: \n542: ### Makefile Target Contract\n543: \n544: ```makefile\n545: # Version and image variables\n546: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo latest)\n547: IMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\n548: TARGETOS ?= linux\n549: TARGETARCH ?= amd64\n550: \n551: # Build targets\n552: .PHONY: all build build-workloadmanager build-router build-picod build-agentd build-agentctl build-agentcube build-agentsandbox\n553: \n554: all: build\n555: \n556: build: generate ## Build all binaries\n557: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n558: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n559: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n560: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n561: \tgo build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n562: \tgo build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n563: \tgo build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n564: \n565: build-workloadmanager: generate ## Build workloadmanager binary only\n566: \tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n567: \n568: build-router: generate ## Build router binary only\n569: \tgo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n570: \n571: build-picod: generate ## Build picod binary only\n572: \tgo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n573: \n574: build-agentd: generate ## Build agentd binary only\n575: \tgo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n576: \n577: build-agentctl: generate ## Build agentctl binary only\n578: \tgo build -o bin/agentctl ./cmd/agentctl\n579: \n580: build-agentcube: generate ## Build agentcube binary only\n581: \tgo build -o bin/agentcube ./cmd/agentcube\n582: \n583: build-agentsandbox: generate ## Build agentsandbox binary only\n584: \tgo build -o bin/agentsandbox ./cmd/agentsandbox\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ### Test Target Contract\n588: \n589: ```makefile\n590: .PHONY: test test-coverage test-race\n591: \n592: test: ## Run unit tests with verbose output\n593: \tgo test -v ./...\n594: \n595: test-coverage: ## Run tests with coverage report\n596: \tgo test -coverprofile=coverage.out ./...\n597: \tgo tool cover -func=coverage.out\n598: \tgo tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n599: \n600: test-race: ## Run tests with race detector\n601: \tgo test -race ./...\n602: ```\n603: \n604: ### Quality Target Contract\n605: \n606: ```makefile\n607: .PHONY: lint fmt vet gen-check gen-copyright\n608: \n609: lint: ## Run golangci-lint\n610: \t$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...\n611: \n612: fmt: ## Format Go files\n613: \tgo fmt ./...\n614: \n615: vet: ## Run go vet\n616: \tgo vet ./...\n617: \n618: gen-check: gen-all ## Verify generated code is up to date\n619: \tgit diff --exit-code\n620: \n621: gen-copyright: ## Generate copyright headers\n622: \thack/update-copyright.sh\n623: ```\n624: \n625: ### Docker Target Contract\n626: \n627: ```makefile\n628: .PHONY: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod docker-build-all \\\n629:         docker-buildx-push docker-buildx-push-router docker-buildx-push-picod\n630: \n631: docker-build: ## Build workloadmanager Docker image\n632: \tdocker build \\\n633: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n634: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n635: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS) \\\n636: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH) \\\n637: \t\t.\n638: \n639: docker-build-router: ## Build router Docker image\n640: \tdocker build \\\n641: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n642: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n643: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS) \\\n644: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH) \\\n645: \t\t.\n646: \n647: docker-build-picod: ## Build picod Docker image\n648: \tdocker build \\\n649: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n650: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n651: \t\t.\n652: \n653: docker-build-all: docker-build docker-build-router docker-build-picod ## Build all Docker images\n654: \n655: docker-buildx-push: ## Build and push workloadmanager multi-arch image\n656: \tdocker buildx build \\\n657: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n658: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n659: \t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=linux \\\n660: \t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=amd64 \\\n661: \t\t--push \\\n662: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n663: \t\t.\n664: \n665: docker-buildx-push-router: ## Build and push router multi-arch image\n666: \tdocker buildx build \\\n667: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n668: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n669: \t\t--push \\\n670: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION) \\\n671: \t\t.\n672: \n673: docker-buildx-push-picod: ## Build and push picod multi-arch image\n674: \tdocker buildx build \\\n675: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n676: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n677: \t\t--push \\\n678: \t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION) \\\n679: \t\t.\n680: ```\n681: \n682: ### E2E Target Contract\n683: \n684: ```makefile\n685: .PHONY: e2e e2e-setup e2e-clean\n686: \n687: e2e: ## Run E2E tests\n688: \t./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh\n689: \n690: e2e-clean: ## Clean up E2E test resources\n691: \tkind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)\n692: \trm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox\n693: ```\n694: \n695: ### Install Target Contract\n696: \n697: ```makefile\n698: .PHONY: install install-workloadmanager install-router install-picod \\\n699:         install-agentd install-agentctl install-agentcube install-agentsandbox\n700: \n701: INSTALL_PREFIX ?= $(shell go env GOPATH)/bin\n702: \n703: install: build ## Install all binaries to INSTALL_PREFIX\n704: \tcp bin/workloadmanager $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n705: \tcp bin/router $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n706: \tcp bin/picod $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n707: \tcp bin/agentd $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n708: \tcp bin/agentctl $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n709: \tcp bin/agentcube $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n710: \tcp bin/agentsandbox $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n711: \n712: install-workloadmanager: build-workloadmanager ## Install workloadmanager binary\n713: \tcp bin/workloadmanager $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n714: \n715: install-router: build-router ## Install router binary\n716: \tcp bin/router $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n717: \n718: install-picod: build-picod ## Install picod binary\n719: \tcp bin/picod $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n720: \n721: install-agentd: build-agentd ## Install agentd binary\n722: \tcp bin/agentd $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n723: \n724: install-agentctl: build-agentctl ## Install agentctl binary\n725: \tcp bin/agentctl $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n726: \n727: install-agentcube: build-agentcube ## Install agentcube binary\n728: \tcp bin/agentcube $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n729: \n730: install-agentsandbox: build-agentsandbox ## Install agentsandbox binary\n731: \tcp bin/agentsandbox $(INSTALL_PREFIX)/\n732: ```\n733: \n734: ### Cross-Compile Target Contract\n735: \n736: ```makefile\n737: .PHONY: build-linux-amd64 build-linux-arm64 build-darwin-amd64 build-darwin-arm64\n738: \n739: build-linux-amd64: generate ## Build for Linux AMD64\n740: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n741: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n742: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n743: \n744: build-linux-arm64: generate ## Build for Linux ARM64\n745: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n746: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n747: \tGOOS=linux GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n748: \n749: build-darwin-amd64: generate ## Build for Darwin AMD64\n750: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n751: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n752: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n753: \n754: build-darwin-arm64: generate ## Build for Darwin ARM64\n755: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n756: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n757: \tGOOS=darwin GOARCH=arm64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n758: ```\n759: \n760: ### Clean Target Contract\n761: \n762: ```makefile\n763: .PHONY: clean clean-test clean-bin\n764: \n765: clean: clean-bin clean-test ## Remove all build artifacts\n766: \trm -f workloadmanager router picod agentd agentctl agentcube agentsandbox\n767: \n768: clean-bin: ## Remove binary directory\n769: \trm -rf bin/\n770: \n771: clean-test: ## Remove test artifacts\n772: \trm -f coverage.out coverage.html\n773: ```\n774: \n775: ### Help Target Contract\n776: \n777: ```makefile\n778: .PHONY: help\n779: \n780: help: ## Display this help screen\n781: \t@awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*##\"; printf \"\\nUsage:\\n  make <target>\\n\\n\"} \\\n782: \t\t/^##@/ { category = substr($$$0, 4); printf \"%-20s\\n\", category } \\\n783: \t\t/^[%a-zA-Z0-9_-]+:.*##/ { target = substr($$$1, 1, length($$$1)-1); \\\n784: \t\tprintf \"  %-20s %s\\n\", target, substr($$$0, index($$$0, \"##\") + 3) } \\\n785: \t\tEND { printf \"\\n\" }' $(MAKEFILE_LIST)\n786: ```\n787: \n788: ### Target Command Interface Schema\n789: \n790: ```yaml\n791: TargetCommand:\n792:   parameters:\n793:     target:\n794:       type: string\n795:       required: true\n796:       values:\n797:         - \"all\"\n798:         - \"build\"\n799:         - \"build-*\"\n800:         - \"test\"\n801:         - \"test-coverage\"\n802:         - \"test-race\"\n803:         - \"lint\"\n804:         - \"fmt\"\n805:         - \"vet\"\n806:         - \"gen-check\"\n807:         - \"gen-copyright\"\n808:         - \"docker-build\"\n809:         - \"docker-build-*\"\n810:         - \"docker-buildx-push-*\"\n811:         - \"e2e\"\n812:         - \"e2e-clean\"\n813:         - \"install\"\n814:         - \"install-*\"\n815:         - \"clean\"\n816:         - \"help\"\n817:         \n818:     variables:\n819:       VERSION:\n820:         type: string\n821:         optional: true\n822:         override: \"make build VERSION=v1.0.0\"\n823:       IMAGE_REPO:\n824:         type: string\n825:         optional: true\n826:         override: \"make docker-build IMAGE_REPO=myrepo\"\n827:       BINDIR:\n828:         type: string\n829:         optional: true\n830:         override: \"make build BINDIR=out/\"\n831:       INSTALL_PREFIX:\n832:         type: string\n833:         optional: true\n834:         override: \"make install INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr/local/bin\"\n835:       TARGETOS:\n836:         type: string\n837:         optional: true\n838:         override: \"make docker-build TARGETOS=darwin\"\n839:       TARGETARCH:\n840:         type: string\n841:         optional: true\n842:         override: \"make docker-build TARGETARCH=arm64\"\n843:         \n844:   outputs:\n845:     binaries:\n846:       type: array\n847:       items: \"bin/*\"\n848:     coverage_files:\n849:       type: array\n850:       items: [\"coverage.out\", \"coverage.html\"]\n851:     docker_images:\n852:       type: array\n853:       items: \"$(IMAGE_REPO)/<name>:$(VERSION)\"\n854:     exit_code:\n855:       type: integer\n856:       values: [0, 1, 2]\n857:       description: \"0=success, 1=failure, 2=make error\"\n858: ```\n859: \n860: ---\n861: \n862: ## Error Handling\n863: \n864: ### Build Error Categories\n865: \n866: | Error Category | Description | Detection | Recovery Action |\n867: |----------------|-------------|-----------|-----------------|\n868: | `GoBuildError` | Go compilation failure | `go build` exit code | Review compilation logs, fix source |\n869: | `GoModError` | Module dependency issues | `go mod` exit code | Run `go mod tidy`, check go.mod |\n870: | `GenerateError` | Code generation failure | `controller-gen` exit | Check pkg/apis/ definitions |\n871: | `LintError` | Linter violations | `golangci-lint` exit | Fix violations, run `fmt` |\n872: | `DockerBuildError` | Docker build failure | `docker build` exit | Check Dockerfile, build context |\n873: | `DockerPushError` | Registry push failure | `docker push` exit | Check registry credentials |\n874: | `KindCreateError` | Kind cluster creation failure | `kind create` exit | Check Docker, Kind version |\n875: | `HelmDeployError` | Helm deployment failure | `helm upgrade` exit | Check chart, values |\n876: | `TestError` | Test failure | `go test` exit | Review test output, fix code |\n877: | `CoverageError` | Coverage below threshold | Coverage percentage | Adjust threshold or add tests |\n878: | `InstallError` | Binary installation failure | `cp` exit code | Check INSTALL_PREFIX permissions |\n879: \n880: ### Makefile Error Detection Pattern\n881: \n882: ```makefile\n883: # Error handling pattern with exit codes\n884: .PHONY: build-safe\n885: \n886: build-safe:\n887: \t@echo \"Building binaries...\"\n888: \t@if ! go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager; then \\\n889: \t\techo \"ERROR: Failed to build workloadmanager\"; \\\n890: \t\texit 1; \\\n891: \tfi\n892: \t@if ! go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router; then \\\n893: \t\techo \"ERROR: Failed to build router\"; \\\n894: \t\texit 1; \\\n895: \tfi\n896: \t@echo \"All binaries built successfully\"\n897: ```\n898: \n899: ### Target Dependency Failure Handling\n900: \n901: ```makefile\n902: # Dependency chain with error propagation\n903: .PHONY: build-all-safe\n904: \n905: build-all-safe: build-workloadmanager-safe build-router-safe build-picod-safe\n906: \t@echo \"All builds completed\"\n907: \n908: build-workloadmanager-safe:\n909: \t@echo \"Building workloadmanager...\"\n910: \t@go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager || (echo \"ERROR: workloadmanager build failed\" && exit 1)\n911: \n912: build-router-safe:\n913: \t@echo \"Building router...\"\n914: \t@go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router || (echo \"ERROR: router build failed\" && exit 1)\n915: \n916: build-picod-safe:\n917: \t@echo \"Building picod...\"\n918: \t@go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod || (echo \"ERROR: picod build failed\" && exit 1)\n919: ```\n920: \n921: ### Docker Build Error Script Pattern\n922: \n923: ```bash\n924: #!/bin/bash\n925: # build-docker-with-error-handling.sh\n926: \n927: set -euo pipefail\n928: \n929: build_docker_image() {\n930:     local dockerfile=\"$1\"\n931:     local tag=\"$2\"\n932:     \n933:     echo \"Building image from $dockerfile...\"\n934:     \n935:     if ! docker build -f \"$dockerfile\" -t \"$tag\" .; then\n936:         echo \"ERROR: Build failed for $dockerfile\"\n937:         \n938:         # Retry without cache\n939:         echo \"Retrying without cache...\"\n940:         if ! docker build -f \"$dockerfile\" -t \"$tag\" . --no-cache; then\n941:             echo \"ERROR: Build failed even with --no-cache\"\n942:             return 1\n943:         fi\n944:     fi\n945:     \n946:     # Verify image size\n947:     local size=$(docker image inspect \"$tag\" --format='{{.Size}}')\n948:     echo \"Image size: $(numfmt --to=iec $size)\"\n949:     \n950:     return 0\n951: }\n952: \n953: main() {\n954:     local failed=0\n955:     \n956:     for image in workloadmanager router picod; do\n957:         local dockerfile=\"docker/Dockerfile\"\n958:         [[ \"$image\" != \"workloadmanager\" ]] && dockerfile=\"docker/Dockerfile.$image\"\n959:         \n960:         if ! build_docker_image \"$dockerfile\" \"agentcube/$image:test\"; then\n961:             failed=1\n962:         fi\n963:     done\n964:     \n965:     [[ $failed -eq 1 ]] && echo \"ERROR: One or more builds failed\" && exit 1\n966:     echo \"All builds completed successfully\"\n967: }\n968: \n969: main\n970: ```\n971: \n972: ### E2E Test Error Recovery\n973: \n974: | Error | Detection | Recovery | Cleanup |\n975: |-------|-----------|----------|---------|\n976: | `KindClusterExists` | `kind get clusters` | Delete and recreate | `kind delete cluster` |\n977: | `ImageLoadFailed` | `kind load` exit code | Rebuild image | `make docker-build-*` |\n978: | `HelmInstallFailed` | `helm upgrade` exit | Check values | `helm uninstall` |\n979: | `PodNotReady` | `kubectl rollout status` | Check pod logs | `kubectl describe pod` |\n980: | `TestFailed` | Test exit code | Collect logs | `collect_component_logs` |\n981: \n982: ### Error Exit Codes\n983: \n984: | Exit Code | Meaning | Action |\n985: |-----------|---------|--------|\n986: | 0 | Success | Continue to next step |\n987: | 1 | General error | Review error message |\n988: | 2 | Make misuse | Check target syntax |\n989: | 77 | Missing dependency | Install required tool |\n990: | 125 | Docker error | Check Docker status |\n991: \n992: ---\n993: \n994: ## Testing Strategy\n995: \n996: ### Test Categories\n997: \n998: | Category | Scope | Tools | Purpose |\n999: |----------|-------|-------|---------|\n1000: | Makefile Syntax | Valid Makefile syntax | `make --dry-run`, shell lint | Verify Makefile parses correctly |\n1001: | Target Execution | All targets work | `make <target>` | Verify each target executes |\n1002: | Binary Output | Binaries compile | `go build`, file existence | Verify binaries exist and run |\n1003: | Test Coverage | Coverage generation | `go test -cover`, `go tool cover` | Verify coverage report generated |\n1004: | Lint Integration | Linter runs | `golangci-lint`, version check | Verify correct linter version |\n1005: | Docker Build | Images build | `docker build`, image inspect | Verify images build correctly |\n1006: | E2E Execution | Full E2E flow | Kind, Helm, Go test | Verify E2E tests pass |\n1007: | Help Output | Help formatting | `make help` output check | Verify help target works |\n1008: | Variable Override | Variable system | `make <target> VAR=value` | Verify variable overrides |\n1009: | Cross-Compile | GOOS/GOARCH builds | File architecture check | Verify cross-compilation |\n1010: \n1011: ### Unit Tests: Makefile Syntax Validation\n1012: \n1013: ```bash\n1014: #!/bin/bash\n1015: # test_makefile_syntax.sh\n1016: \n1017: test_makefile_exists() {\n1018:     if [[ ! -f \"Makefile\" ]]; then\n1019:         echo \"FAIL: Makefile does not exist\"\n1020:         return 1\n1021:     fi\n1022:     echo \"PASS: Makefile exists\"\n1023:     return 0\n1024: }\n1025: \n1026: test_makefile_parses() {\n1027:     if ! make --dry-run help 2>/dev/null; then\n1028:         echo \"FAIL: Makefile does not parse\"\n1029:         return 1\n1030:     fi\n1031:     echo \"PASS: Makefile parses correctly\"\n1032:     return 0\n1033: }\n1034: \n1035: test_phony_declarations() {\n1036:     local phony_targets=$(grep -E \"^\\.PHONY:\" Makefile | sed 's/.PHONY: //')\n1037:     local expected=\"all build test clean lint fmt vet gen-check e2e e2e-clean install help\"\n1038:     \n1039:     for target in $expected; do\n1040:         if ! echo \"$phony_targets\" | grep -qw \"$target\"; then\n1041:             echo \"FAIL: Missing .PHONY declaration for $target\"\n1042:             return 1\n1043:         fi\n1044:     done\n1045:     echo \"PASS: All expected targets have .PHONY declarations\"\n1046:     return 0\n1047: }\n1048: \n1049: test_variable_defaults() {\n1050:     # Test IMAGE_REPO default\n1051:     if ! grep -q \"IMAGE_REPO ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube\" Makefile; then\n1052:         echo \"FAIL: Missing IMAGE_REPO default\"\n1053:         return 1\n1054:     fi\n1055:     \n1056:     # Test VERSION default\n1057:     if ! grep -qE \"VERSION ?= .*git describe\" Makefile; then\n1058:         echo \"FAIL: Missing VERSION git describe default\"\n1059:         return 1\n1060:     fi\n1061:     \n1062:     echo \"PASS: Variables have correct defaults\"\n1063:     return 0\n1064: }\n1065: \n1066: test_help_target() {\n1067:     if ! grep -q \"^help:\" Makefile; then\n1068:         echo \"FAIL: Missing help target\"\n1069:         return 1\n1070:     fi\n1071:     \n1072:     # Check help target uses awk for formatting\n1073:     if ! grep -q \"awk.*BEGIN.*FS.*:.*##\" Makefile; then\n1074:         echo \"FAIL: Help target missing awk formatter\"\n1075:         return 1\n1076:     fi\n1077:     \n1078:     echo \"PASS: Help target defined correctly\"\n1079:     return 0\n1080: }\n1081: \n1082: test_target_documentation() {\n1083:     # Check for ## comment pattern\n1084:     local documented_targets=$(grep -E \"^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+:.*##\" Makefile | wc -l)\n1085:     \n1086:     if [[ $documented_targets -lt 10 ]]; then\n1087:         echo \"FAIL: Too few documented targets (expected >= 10, got $documented_targets)\"\n1088:         return 1\n1089:     fi\n1090:     \n1091:     echo \"PASS: Targets have ## documentation comments\"\n1092:     return 0\n1093: }\n1094: \n1095: main() {\n1096:     local failed=0\n1097:     \n1098:     test_makefile_exists || failed=1\n1099:     test_makefile_parses || failed=1\n1100:     test_phony_declarations || failed=1\n1101:     test_variable_defaults || failed=1\n1102:     test_help_target || failed=1\n1103:     test_target_documentation || failed=1\n1104:     \n1105:     if [[ $failed -eq 1 ]]; then\n1106:         echo \"SYNTAX TESTS FAILED\"\n1107:         exit 1\n1108:     fi\n1109:     \n1110:     echo \"ALL SYNTAX TESTS PASSED\"\n1111:     exit 0\n1112: }\n1113: \n1114: main\n1115: ```\n1116: \n1117: ### Integration Tests: Target Execution\n1118: \n1119: ```bash\n1120: #!/bin/bash\n1121: # test_makefile_targets.sh\n1122: \n1123: set -euo pipefail\n1124: \n1125: cleanup() {\n1126:     rm -rf bin/ coverage.out coverage.html 2>/dev/null || true\n1127: }\n1128: \n1129: trap cleanup EXIT\n1130: \n1131: test_build_target() {\n1132:     echo \"Testing make build...\"\n1133:     \n1134:     if ! make build; then\n1135:         echo \"FAIL: make build failed\"\n1136:         return 1\n1137:     fi\n1138:     \n1139:     # Verify all binaries exist\n1140:     for binary in workloadmanager router picod agentd agentctl agentcube agentsandbox; do\n1141:         if [[ ! -f \"bin/$binary\" ]]; then\n1142:             echo \"FAIL: bin/$binary not found after make build\"\n1143:             return 1\n1144:         fi\n1145:         echo \"PASS: bin/$binary exists\"\n1146:     done\n1147:     \n1148:     return 0\n1149: }\n1150: \n1151: test_single_binary_target() {\n1152:     local target=\"$1\"\n1153:     local binary=\"$2\"\n1154:     \n1155:     echo \"Testing make $target...\"\n1156:     \n1157:     rm -f \"bin/$binary\"\n1158:     \n1159:     if ! make \"$target\"; then\n1160:         echo \"FAIL: make $target failed\"\n1161:         return 1\n1162:     fi\n1163:     \n1164:     if [[ ! -f \"bin/$binary\" ]]; then\n1165:         echo \"FAIL: bin/$binary not found after make $target\"\n1166:         return 1\n1167:     fi\n1168:     \n1169:     echo \"PASS: make $target built bin/$binary\"\n1170:     return 0\n1171: }\n1172: \n1173: test_test_target() {\n1174:     echo \"Testing make test...\"\n1175:     \n1176:     if ! make test; then\n1177:         echo \"FAIL: make test failed\"\n1178:         return 1\n1179:     fi\n1180:     \n1181:     echo \"PASS: make test executed successfully\"\n1182:     return 0\n1183: }\n1184: \n1185: test_coverage_target() {\n1186:     echo \"Testing make test-coverage...\"\n1187:     \n1188:     if ! make test-coverage; then\n1189:         echo \"FAIL: make test-coverage failed\"\n1190:         return 1\n1191:     fi\n1192:     \n1193:     if [[ ! -f \"coverage.out\" ]]; then\n1194:         echo \"FAIL: coverage.out not generated\"\n1195:         return 1\n1196:     fi\n1197:     \n1198:     if [[ ! -f \"coverage.html\" ]]; then\n1199:         echo \"FAIL: coverage.html not generated\"\n1200:         return 1\n1201:   