elp 2>/dev/null` |\n| Phase 16 | `make build && ls bin/workloadmanager` |\n| Phase 17 | `make test-coverage && test -f coverage.out` |\n| Phase 18 | `make lint` |\n| Phase 19 | `make docker-build-all IMAGE_REPO=test VERSION=test` |\n| Phase 20 | `make clean && test ! -d bin/` |\n| Phase 21 | `make help | grep \"Build\"` |\n| Phase 22 | `make build VERSION=test-override BINDIR=test-bin` |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Makefile has all 9 variable definitions (IMAGE_REPO, VERSION, TARGETOS, TARGETARCH, BINDIR, GO_VERSION, GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION, CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION, INSTALL_PREFIX)\n- [ ] Makefile has all 7 binary build targets (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox)\n- [ ] Makefile has 4 cross-compile targets (linux-amd64, linux-arm64, darwin-amd64, darwin-arm64)\n- [ ] Makefile has test, test-coverage, test-race targets\n- [ ] Makefile has fmt, vet, lint, gen-check, gen-copyright targets\n- [ ] Makefile has generate, gen-crd, gen-client, gen-all targets\n- [ ] Makefile has docker-build, docker-build-router, docker-build-picod, docker-build-all targets\n- [ ] Makefile has docker-buildx-push, docker-buildx-push-router, docker-buildx-push-picod targets\n- [ ] Makefile has kind-load, kind-load-router, kind-load-picod, kind-load-all targets\n- [ ] Makefile has e2e, e2e-setup, e2e-clean targets\n- [ ] Makefile has install and 7 install-* targets\n- [ ] Makefile has clean, clean-bin, clean-test targets\n- [ ] Makefile has help target with awk formatter\n- [ ] All targets have ## documentation comments\n- [ ] Categories marked with ##@ headers (Build, Test, Quality, Docker, E2E, Codegen, Install)\n- [ ] SHELL set to bash with pipefail\n- [ ] .NOTPARALLEL for docker-build-all\n- [ ] go-install-tool macro for tool installation\n- [ ] make build produces all 7 binaries\n- [ ] make test runs unit tests\n- [ ] make test-coverage generates coverage.out and coverage.html\n- [ ] make docker-build-all builds all 3 images\n- [ ] make help displays formatted help screen\n- [ ] Variable overrides work (VERSION, IMAGE_REPO, BINDIR)\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Lines | Description |\n|------|--------|-------|-------------|\n| `Makefile` | Modify | ~250 | Expand from 71 lines to full build system with all targets |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Help Target Pattern\n\n```makefile\nhelp: ## Display this help screen\n\t@awk 'BEGIN {FS = \":.*##\"; printf \"\\nUsage:\\n  make <target>\\n\\n\"} \\\n\t\t/^##@/ { category = substr($$0, 4); printf \"%-20s\\n\", category } \\\n\t\t/^[%a-zA-Z0-9_-]+:.*##/ { target = substr($$1, 1, length($$1)-1); \\\n\t\tprintf \"  %-20s %s\\n\", target, substr($$0, index($$0, \"##\") + 3) } \\\n\t\tEND { printf \"\\n\" }' $(MAKEFILE_LIST)\n```\n\n### go-install-tool Macro\n\n```makefile\ndefine go-install-tool\n@[ -f \"$(1)\" ] || { \\\nset -e ; \\\necho \"Installing $(2)\" ; \\\nGOBIN=$(LOCALBIN) go install $(2)@$(3) ; }\nendef\n```\n\n### Binary Build Pattern\n\n```makefile\nbuild-workloadmanager: generate ## Build workloadmanager binary only\n\tgo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n```\n\n### Docker Build Pattern\n\n```makefile\ndocker-build: ## Build workloadmanager Docker image\n\tdocker build \\\n\t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n\t\t-t $(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION) \\\n\t\t--build-arg TARGETOS=$(TARGETOS) \\\n\t\t--build-arg TARGETARCH=$(TARGETARCH) \\\n\t\t.\n```\n\n### Cross-Compile Pattern\n\n```makefile\nbuild-linux-amd64: generate ## Build for Linux AMD64\n\tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\n\tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n\tGOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Timeline\n\n| Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n|-------|-------|--------|------------|\n| Phase 1: Variable System | T1.1-T1.9 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 2: Build Targets | T2.1-T2.10 | Pending | 0% |\n| Phase 3: